```

**CSS cascade correctness**: For dark themes, the `[data-theme]` block and the `@variant dark` block both apply (`.dark` class is set by `applyAppTheme`). `[data-theme]` wins on conflicting vars (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`). Non-conflicting dark-mode vars (`--muted`, `--card`, `--border`, etc.) come from the existing `@variant dark` block — they reference `--background` internally so they automatically pick up the theme's override.

**Update sidebar background** (already in index.css, the `<Sidebar>` uses `bg-card` via Tailwind; add a CSS rule for sidebar background usage):
```css
/* Wire --sidebar-bg into the sidebar surface */
[data-sidebar] {
  background-color: var(--sidebar-bg);
}
```
*(Check actual sidebar DOM attribute in `apps/web/src/components/ui/sidebar.tsx` to use the right selector; if `data-sidebar` doesn't exist, fall back to adding a `.sidebar-surface` class or leave this for a follow-up — the theme vars will still be defined and accessible)*

